title: For Sale:  Pedersoli Bristlen A Morges .44 Cal BP
postcontent: These sell for $3375.00 new & have to be special ordered to get one. Feel free to made a trade offer on this one. Made by Pedersoli in Italy, this is a reproduction of an 1847 elegant target rifle produced by Swiss rifle maker Marc Bristlen in the town of Morges. .44 Caliber blackpowder – browned 29 1/2" tapered octagon heavy barrel measuring 1 ¼” at breech to 1" at muzzle. The bore is button rifled .008" deep, 1-26" twist, 4 lands .442" and 4 grooves .458". Nipple is 1/4x28 and uses #11 percussion caps - recommended load: 40 grains of FFFg black and .440 conical bullet. The front sight is 3/8" dovetail, hooded post and rear sight is Creedmore style adjustable for windage and elevation. It has a double set/double phase triggers - palm rest – steel ramrod - case colored hardware - American walnut satin finished half-stock with a 3 ½” drop - 13" trigger LOP - overall length is 48 1/2" and total weight is 15 1/2 lbs. The wood has gorgeous dark grain with some burl & birds-eyes. Mechanically sound; functions like new & the bore is mint. It remains in high condition with only minor handling marks but no damage of any kind. The original owner has only fired it on a couple of occasions & always stored it properly. This is a beautiful rifle & will be dead accurate. It looks even better in person than in the pictures!

title: For Sale:  PSA AR15 on Aero Lower
postcontent: For sale is my PSA AR15 built on an Aero Lower.The upper is a 16" with a midlength gas system. The barrel is the GI profile, 1:7 twist, and nitrided for corrosion resistance and lifespan. Gas block is a standard F height A2 front sight block. The handguard is a UTG pro 9.7" quad rail. It's the clamp style that presses down on the barrel nut and handguard cap instead of just sitting in place. The bolt carrier assembly is fully nitrided. The charging handle is the Strike Industries ARCH, not the $10 one that every AR has on it.The lower is an Aero Precision, which has a nylon tipped screw to tension the upper against the lower. This lets you set how much play there is between the two receivers. The lower parts are all standard milspec except for the trigger and the stock. The trigger is one of the PSA polished triggers and as such as no take up or slack, and resets positively. The stock is a M4 style, but has a QD sling mount on either side so you don't have to use the sling loop on the bottom. Buffer tube is a 6-position mil-spec, buffer and buffer tube are standard carbine parts, and the buffer tube is new with less than 100 rounds through it. On the lower I also have a Magpul BAD lever on the bolt release, allowing you to drop the bolt with your trigger finger.The rifle also has rail covers, a QD sling mount on the rail, and a Magpul MS4 (I believe) OD Green adjustable sling.Included with the rifle are 10 USGI magazines, three of which have Magpul Ranger Plates on them, a Plano 42" hard case, and a 350 lumen weapon light with high, low, and strobe settings as well as a lockout.Pictured on the rifle are a Streamlight HLX weapon light and a Vortex Crossfire red dot sight. The HLX is a programmable 1,000 lumen, 27,000 candela weapon light that takes either 2 CR123s, or 1 18650 rechargeable. The Vortex Crossfire RDS is a micro pattern red dot sight with 11 brightness settings and a 7,000 hour battery life on setting 7. I'll include the HLX on the rifle for $700 total, the Crossfire for $750, or both for $850.It's been a good rifle, I just need the money much more than the rifle right now. Contact me through text at (573) 644-3203. I'd be happy to tell you more about the gun or send additional pictures on request. Have a great day and stay safe.
